cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.LG 

This paper deals with the problem of estimating hand-object manipulations from RGB images, which involves computer vision, robotics, and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel contact loss that favors physically plausible hand-object constellations, which involves robotics and control, making cs.RO (Robotics) the second most likely sub-category. The paper also uses grasp quality metrics to evaluate the performance of the model, which involves graphics and visualization, making cs.GR (Computer Graphics) the third most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes an end-to-end learnable model that exploits a new dataset, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) the fourth most likely sub-category. Finally, the paper also discusses the transferability of the ObMan-trained models to real data, which involves machine learning and statistics, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) the fifth most likely sub-category.
